description: Fragment of a clay tablet. Omens. 14 lines of inscription. Neo-Assyrian.

content.value: If a man suffers from an acute fever (and) a throbbing temple, [before it becomes severe for him: in order to heal him], you take dirt from the doorjambs? of the city? gate?, [. . .] with [oil, you anoint him (with the mixture), and then he will recover].

parts.text: If a man suffers from an acute fever (and) a throbbing temple, [before it becomes severe for him: in order to heal him], you take dirt from the doorjambs? of the city? gate?, [. . .] with [oil, you anoint him (with the mixture), and then he will recover].

content.value: If a man DITTO (= suffers from an acute fever and a throbbing temple) (and continues to) have a temperature: in order to heal him, [you continually anoint him] with @i{aprušu}-plant in oil. You pound [@i{ankinūtu}-plant], you heat it up in beer, you anoint him with it, [you keep a watch on him, and then he will recover].
